-- variables
2 types
1.Primitive Type
2.Reference Type

Primitive type -> int, float,double, char, boolean (stack)
Reference type -> String, array, object memory(stack) that points to the (heap)

The Stack: Holds the variable name and the specific memory address (the "pointer").
The Heap: Holds the actual data (the characters in the String, the elements in the Array,
or the fields of the Object).

